Velocity
Definition	A measure of the average amount of work  (in story points or other units) that is completed per unit of time (e.g., sprint, day, week, month).
Calculated by:	Only items meeting the “definition of done” are included in the calculations. No partial credit is given for work not completed.
Purpose	Calculate how much work is done in sprint.
Team Velocity
How often calculated.	End of Sprint
Calculated by:	The average number of story points the development team completes each sprint
Purpose	Knowing the team velocity allows the Scrum Master to predict the final completion date of the project, and allows the team to make reasonable commitments regarding the number of story points to agree to work on the upcoming sprint.



Capacity
Definition	A measure of the maximum amount of work that a development team expects to produce in a given sprint. This calculation is based on what resources are available at the specific time of the calculation.
Purpose	Make sure a team is not given more work in a sprint than they can do.

